              "free_text": [
                " Neutron beam from the horizontal experimental",
                " hole incident into a NaCl(200) crystal monochromator.",
                "After Bragg diffraction by the monochromator, the",
                " 0.0253 eV monochromatic neutron beam was obtained",
                " which passed through a simple chopper monochromator",
                " to reduce the higher-order diffracted neutrons",
                " component."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Uranium was electroplated on a platinum foil.",
                "The uranium layer was 26 mm in diameter, 400 ug/cm2",
                " in thickness.",
                "The total weight was",
                "  2.1132 mg for the 233U sample,",
                "  1.9983 mg for the 235U sample(1),",
                "  2.1602 mg for the 235U sample(2).",
                "The isotopic composition for the samples by mass",
                " spectrographic analysis was as follows:",
                "----------------------------------------------------",
                "Isotope  233U sample  235U sample(1)  235U sample(2)",
                "----------------------------------------------------",
                " 233U    99.0+/-0.5",
                " 234U     0.4+/-0.1      1.15+/-0.10      1.0+/-0.1",
                " 235U     0.4+/-0.1     90.0 +/-0.9      90.5+/-0.9",
                " 236U                    0.15+/-0.10",
                " 238U     0.2+/-0.1      8.4 +/-0.7       8.5+/-0.8",
                "----------------------------------------------------"
              ]
            }
          ],
